  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p>\n<p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p>\n<p>Skim through these steps</p>\n<p>Wash your fruit and veg</p>\n<p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Ensure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 mins)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2103.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2103.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2103.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2103.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2103.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p>\n<p>Boil half a kettle</p>\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p>\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong> diced chicken</strong> and most of the<strong> roasted garlic paste</strong> (save some for later) with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 30 secs</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2103.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2103.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2103.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2103.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2103.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve 1/2<span class=\"text-danger\"> [1]</span><strong> Knorr chicken stock cube</strong> in 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong></p>\n<p>Add the<strong> dried chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and<strong> tomato paste</strong> to the chicken and cook for 1-2 min</p>\n<p>Tip: Add more<strong> olive oil</strong> if the pan is looking a little dry</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2103.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2103.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2103.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2103.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2103.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a separate, large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong></p>\n<p>Once the pan is hot, add the<strong> potatoes</strong> to the pan with the <strong>smoked paprika</strong> and season generously with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>black pepper</strong> </p>\n<p>Cook for 6 min or until crisp and cooked through – these are your <strong>paprika potatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2103.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2103.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2103.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2103.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2103.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> chicken stock</strong> to the chicken pan and cook for a further 3-4 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>tomato &amp; garlic chicken</strong> </p>\n<p>Note: Please ensure you cook your chicken thoroughly (until there’s no pink meat and it’s piping hot!) as cooking equipment varies</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2103.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2103.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2103.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2103.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2103.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>remaining garlic paste</strong> to a bowl with the <strong>mayonnaise</strong>, <strong>half</strong> the<strong> cider vinegar</strong> and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[3 tbsp]</span> <strong>water</strong></p>\n<p>Give everything a good mix up and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>black pepper</strong> – this is your <strong>garlic aioli </strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
